The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Speaker ashamed

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Dec. 7: He implored, he threatened, he even offered his chair to them. Finally, Somnath Chatterjee could take it no longer and blurted out: I am ashamed to be the Speaker of this House.

 Chatterjee had had a tough time last week with the House repeatedly erupting over the Iraqi oil-for-food payoffs scandal, leading to serial adjournments. Though the Opposition allowed Parliament to function, after Natwar Singhs resignation as minister, there was no respite for the Speaker.

 The NDA made it clear quickly enough that it would not let go of the Volcker issue.

 The leader of the Opposition, L.K. Advani, raised the controversy after zero hour. Natwar Singh has given NDA the credit for his resignation, Advani quipped.

 At once the Congress members, joined by the Left, stood up and began shouting back.

 When some Opposition members asked the Speaker to control the Treasury benches, Chatterjee shot back: Why dont you come and sit here and control the House?

 Then Advani chose to mention Sonia Gandhis name. Natwar Singh has resigned. The Congress president should also step down till the inquiry is over, he said, prompting bedlam.

 After futile appeals for order, an exasperated Chatterjee declared: I am ashamed.... 




